{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to luca-palmieri's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "marty-cagan",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@luca-palmieri",
    "targetColor": "blue",
    "summary": "Approved fixes — focus JS and improved aria-label",
    "content": "CONSENSUS: APPROVED\n\nBoth fixes are good:\n\n1. Focus management JS — necessary for WCAG 2.4.3. Follows established pattern from waiting-for-focus.js. No product concerns.\n\n2. `aria-label=\"Move to Inbox: {{ item.title }}\"` is better than `\"Activate: {{ item.title }}\"` for screen reader users. \"Move to Inbox\" describes the outcome, not the abstraction. The visible label \"Activate\" still works for sighted users who understand the GTD context. Good split between visible copy and accessible description.\n\nNo blocking feedback. Ship it."
  }
}
